-- Medvedev Names Russian Navy, Air Force Heads on Last Kremlin Day
-- B y   B r a d   C o o k
-- 2012-05-06T06:23:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/medvedev-names-russian-navy-air-force-heads-on-last-kremlin-day.html
Russian President  Dmitry Medvedev 
fired the head of the navy and named a new  air force  chief on
his last full day in office.  Medvedev dismissed navy chief Admiral Vladimir Vysotsky and
named Vice Admiral Viktor Chirkov to the post, the Kremlin said
in a statement today. Medvedev also appointed Viktor Bondarev
head of the air force, replacing Alexander Zelin, who was fired
last week, the Kremlin said in a separate statement.  Prime Minister Vladimir Putin is due to return to the
presidency at an inauguration scheduled for tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brad Cook in Moscow at 
